    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hello, yes good point. IE9 has no history object: http://caniuse.com/#feat=history and there is no good polyfill because the feature of having clean URLS (without #) in IE9 just doesn't exists.\n\nTo fix this, you can use the # in IE9.\n\nYou can instantiate urlSync with useHash: true for IE9. We do not do it automatically.\n\n``` js\n  urlSync: {\n    trackedParameters: [\n      'query',\n      'page',\n      'attribute:*'\n    ],\n    useHash: window.history && 'pushState' in window.history ? false : true,\n  }\n```\n\nLet me know how it goes.\n",
